I saw a couple which could be construed as images in the one series you had
from SEA, but nothing that knocked me over the head yet.  I am going to have
to see a larger sample size before I determine if what you have witnessed is
in fact a form or not.  I cannot accept an image as paranormal without
knowing where it sits among the bulk of audio files.  If every file has
multiple faces, the I would have  to say that there is nothing there.

So, I will certainly keep testing with my copy and hopefully something will
really pop for me.  I have run through about ten files (EVP and GBC) so far
for intensive study and I still haven&#39;t got anything that I would consider a
positive hit.  I need an actual formed face, not portions thereof, to
consider an image real.  This is the only way to discount visual matrixing.

I have high hopes for this though!

Tim

